By Amen Gajira  Kafanchan (Kaduna) A former Editor-In-Chief of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), Mr Shehu Abui, is dead. Abui died at 74. Abui, who served as Editor-in-chief between 2001 and 2006, was until his death the Dan Masani Manchok, (Leader of the learnered) under the Moro’a Chiefdom in Southern Kaduna. His son, Ibrahim, who confirmed the development to NAN , said his father died at a hospital in Jos in the early hours of Wednesday after a brief illness. “My father was admitted in Bingham University Teaching Hospital, Jos, on Monday and I travelled to Jos from Abuja yesterday to donate blood. “But unfortunately, he gave up the ghost at about 1.25 a.m. on Wednesday,” he added Abui, a native of Manchok, Kaura Local Government Area of Kaduna State is survived by his wife and three children. (NAN) By Thompson Yamput Jos - A Federal High Court sitting in Jos on Wednesday ordered the Chief Medical Director (CMD) of Barau Dikko Teaching Hospital, Kaduna to produce documented evidences to back his claim that a suspect, Nanpon Sambo is “dead.” Justice Dorcas Agishi, the presiding judge gave the order… February 19, 2020 In "News" By Philip Yatai   Jere   -     Kaduna State Government with support from Islamic Development Bank (IDB) is constructing six Science Secondary Schools at the cost of N761.7 million to promote science and technology education. The State Commissioner for Education, Science and Technology, Ja’afaru Sani, said on Friday in Jere after… April 20, 2018 In "News" By Moses Kolo Kafanchan (Kaduna) - Kaduna State Gov. Nasir El-Rufai, has commended Moro’a community in Kaura Local Government Area for keeping peace in the face of insecurity that bedeviled the area in recent past. El-Rufai who gave the commendation at the 2020 Annual Moro’a Cultural Festival held at Manchok… January 4, 2020 In "News"